article.headline: Indiana 96, Stony Brook 66
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Cody Zeller scored 16 points in his college debut and Victor Oladipo had a career-high 16 points Friday night, leading Indiana to a 96-66 rout of Stony Brook. The Hoosiers (1-0) have now won 14 consecutive season-openers and 27 straight home-openers. The Seawolves (0-1) were led by Anthony Jackson with 14 points and hung in the game early. After giving up an 18-14 lead, an ugly sequence turned the game. Stony Brook's Al Rapier drew one foul and the Seawolves' Danny Carter was ejected when a replay review showed he had intentionally punched Zeller in the midsection during the same possession. Indiana made three free throws on four attempts, starting an 18-4 run that made it 40-25. Stony Brook never got back within double digits.
